I'm proud to announce the winner of our 2022 Congressional Art Competition: Noura Ibrahim from 
@Hamilton_High!

Her piece, titled "Immigration," will be displayed in the U.S. Capitol representing #AZ09. Thank you to all the talented young artists for your submissions! https://t.co/AB5AR8oaSZ

Last week, I held a roundtable with Arizona seniors. Their message for Congress? Stop playing political games while prescription drug costs skyrocket.

During tomorrow's State of the Union, I expect 
@POTUS to make lowering drug prices a priority. https://t.co/snYfzNqwII

Struggling to pay rent or utilities during the pandemic?

@maricopacounty received $46 million in rental assistance funding from the COVID relief bill passed last December—with an expected $30 million in additional assistance from the #AmericanRescuePlan. 

Learn more and apply⬇️

Congress created the Payroll Support Program to preserve critical aviation jobs + support workers.

@FlyingWithSara shared the story of a Phoenix flight attendant who, when PSP lapsed + forced furloughs, had to take riskier, more frequent shifts. 

She died last week from COVID. https://t.co/lClY5aMRzU

Gabby turned unimaginable pain into a force for progress, 
@GiffordsCourage, and continues to lead the fight to end gun violence in our communities. 

The movement has grown stronger every year. This Congress must act.
